{
  "stem": "3952.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I signed it with my full signature, and he took it away to this Shia, and sure enough, for about two weeks, every day after the soup where we were in the camp, we got another soup from this guy, from this Shia.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This was-- you can't imagine what a bowl of soup means in-- in-- in Wolfsberg, in-- in a labor camp.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "After two weeks, this Tully Lazerovitch comes and says, Itzo says bitter.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What is bitter?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He said, there is a guy from our city, from our town, from Sighet.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "His name is Otzi Mendelovich, and he promised Shia two coins he's going to give him every day.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And Shia starts giving the soup to Otzi.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So he says now, take another piece of paper, and you promise him three coins every day.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So he gave me another piece of paper, and I write.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And while I am writing, he says, write four coins, so that he cannot compete with you-- with-- with us.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And sure enough, I wrote four coins for every bowl of soup.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I would give him four coins.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And after the war, I go to [NON-ENGLISH], to my rabbi, and I meet this Shia there, and we look at each other, and we hug each other, and we both start laughing, burst out into laughter to say that I promised him, where am I going to get the gold coins?",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I never had any gold coins.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Where am I going to get them?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Didn't he know that we didn't have gold coins?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But he wanted to believe the gold coins, I wanted to-- to have the soup.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So I find this is a very funny situation that some funny situations would-- would happen in-- in-- in the camps.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
